		<div class="contentDetailBody">
<span style="text-transform:uppercase;"></span><BR>
March 31, 2009 &mdash; <p>Prof. Antonio Ortega has agreed to serve as Associate Chair of Ming Hsieh EE-Systems beginning August 16, 2009.&nbsp; Antonio served previously as Associate Chair from 2004 though 2007, Department Systems co-Chair Alexander Sawchuk announced.</p>
<p><span style="display: block;">
<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0" style="width: 202px; height: 239px;" class="tableCaptionedImageRight">
    <tbody>
        <tr>
            <td class="tableCaptionedImageImage"><img width="200" height="256" src="/assets/032/52091.jpg" alt="" /></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td class="tableCaptionedImageCaption">
            <h6>Antonio Ortega will resume Associate Chair duties in August.</h6>
            </td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>
</table>
</span>Sawchuk said the duties of the post included&nbsp; working closely with student affairs staff, and administering Ph.D. programs, advisement, teaching assistants, fellowships, scholarships and financial aid, faculty teaching assignments, and student recruiting and retention events.</p>
<p>Ortega joined USC in 1994 after receiving his Ph.D. from Columbia University.&nbsp; He is a member and past director of the Signal and Image Processing Institute (SIPI).&nbsp; His research interests are in signal analysis and compression, including applications such as image and video coding, information processing in sensor networks and distributed classification/recognition.&nbsp;</p>
<p>He is the author or co-author of nearly 200 publications in international journals and conferences.&nbsp; He was won several best paper and other awards, and was elected an IEEE Fellow in 2007.</p>
<p>Todd Brun has been Associate Chair since June 2007.&nbsp; He will be on sabbatical for the Fall 2009 and Spring 2010 semesters.</p>
<p>&quot;I welcome Antonio Ortega to his new appointment as Associate Chair, and express my gratitude to Prof. Todd Brun for his outstanding performance in this position since June 2007, said Sawchuk. I greatly appreciate Todd's skill, dedication and service during his two years in this position.&quot;</p>		</div>
